3e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightgallery\" href=\"/2025-10-01-cve-2022-21661/detect.png\" title=\"Detect\" data-thumbnail=\"/2025-10-01-cve-2022-21661/detect.png\" data-sub-html=\"\u003ch2\u003eResponse shows delay caused by payload execution\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eDetect\u003c/p\u003e\"\u003e\u003cimg  loading=\"lazy\" src='/2025-10-01-cve-2022-21661/detect.png' srcset=\"/2025-10-01-cve-2022-21661/detect_hu_1c7d5def755e00b5.webp 800w, /2025-10-01-cve-2022-21661/detect_hu_2615643d2f4824a8.webp 1200w, /2025-10-01-cve-2022-21661/detect_hu_143da15c4570bda5.webp 1600w\"  alt=\"Detect\" height=\"267\" width=\"433\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cfigcaption class=\"image-caption\"\u003eResponse shows delay caused by payload execution\u003c/figcaption\u003e\n\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"conclusion\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"#conclusion\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e47 Conclusion\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe \u003cstrong\u003eCVE-2022-21661\u003c/strong\u003e vulnerability in \u003cstrong\u003eWordPress Core\u003c/strong\u003e, prior to version \u003cstrong\u003e5.8.3\u003c/strong\u003e (affecting versions back to \u003cstrong\u003e3.7.37\u003c/strong\u003e), stems from improper \u003cstrong\u003esanitization\u003c/strong\u003e in \u003ccode\u003eWP_Query\u003c/code\u003e, leading to a potential SQL Injection vulnerability.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"references\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"#references\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e48 References\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://portswigger.net/web-security/sql-injection/cheat-sheet\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eSQL Injection cheat sheet - PortSwigger\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2022-21661\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eCVE-2022-21661 Detail\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"notes\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"#notes\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e49 Notes\u003c/h2\u003e",
        "language": "en"
    }
    {
        "title" : "CVE-2025-2011 Analysis \u0026 POC",
        "date_published" : "2025-09-30T19:08:00+07:00",
        "date_modified" : "2025-09-30T19:08:00+07:00",
        "id" : "http://localhost:1313/2025-09-30-cve-2025-2011/",
        "url" : "http://localhost:1313/2025-09-30-cve-2025-2011/",
        "content_html" : "\u003cp\u003eThe vulnerability occurs in the \u003cstrong\u003eDepicter Slider\u003c/strong\u003e WordPress plugin prior to version \u003cstrong\u003e3.6.2\u003c/strong\u003e. This could allow an attacker to directly interact with your database, potentially leading to data theft or manipulation.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCVE ID\u003c/strong\u003e: \u003ca href=\"https://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2025-2011\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eCVE-2025-2011\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eProduct\u003c/strong\u003e: \u003ca href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/depicter/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eWordPress Depicter Slider Plugin\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVulnerability Type\u003c/strong\u003e: SQL Injection\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAffected Versions\u003c/strong\u003e: \u0026lt;= 3.6.1\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCVSS severity\u003c/strong\u003e: High (9.3)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRequired Privilege\u003c/strong\u003e: Unauthenticated\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"requirements\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"#requirements\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e31 Requirements\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://w41bu1.github.io/blog/2025-08-21-wordpress-local-and-debugging/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLocal WordPress and Debugging\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDepicter Slider\u003c/strong\u003e: v3.6.1 (vulnerable) and v3.6.2 (patched)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDiff tool\u003c/strong\u003e: \u003cstrong\u003emeld\u003c/strong\u003e or any other comparison tool to visualize differences between versions\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"analysis\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"#analysis\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e32 Analysis\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe root cause is that the application directly injects data from a \u003cstrong\u003eGET\u003c/strong\u003e request into the SQL query without proper sanitization or escaping.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"patch-diff\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"#patch-diff\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e32.1 Patch Diff\u003c/h3\u003e\u003cp\u003eUse any diff tool to compare the vulnerable and patched versions.\nA notable difference appears in \u003cstrong\u003eapp/src/Controllers/Ajax/LeadsAjaxController.php\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eindex\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003elist\u003c/code\u003e, and \u003ccode\u003eexport\u003c/code\u003e are three key functions inside the \u003ccode\u003eLeadsAjaxController\u003c/code\u003e class.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"code-block highlight is-closed show-line-numbers  tw-group tw-my-2\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"\n    \n    tw-flex \n    tw-flex-row\n    tw-flex-1 \n    tw-justify-between \n    tw-w-full tw-bg-bgColor-secondary\n    \"\u003e      \n    \u003cbutton \n      class=\"\n        code-block-button\n        tw-mx-2 \n        tw-flex\n        tw-flex-row\n        tw-flex-1\"\n      aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\n          \u003cdiv class=\"group-[.is-open]:tw-rotate-90 tw-transition-[transform] tw-duration-500 tw-ease-in-out print:!tw-hidden tw-w-min tw-h-min tw-my-1 tw-mx-1\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"icon\"\n    xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 320 512\"\u003e\u003c!-- Font Awesome Free 5.15.4 by @fontawesome - https://fontawesome.com License - https://fontawesome.com/license/free (Icons: CC BY 4.0, Fonts: SIL OFL 1.1, Code: MIT License) --\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M285.476 272.971L91.132 467.314c-9.373 9.373-24.569 9.373-33.941 0l-22.667-22.667c-9.357-9.357-9.375-24.522-.04-33.901L188.505 256 34.484 101.255c-9.335-9.379-9.317-24.544.04-33.901l22.667-22.667c9.373-9.373 24.569-9.373 33.941 0L285.475 239.03c9.373 9.372 9.373 24.568.001 33.941z\"/\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n          \u003cp class=\"tw-select-none !tw-my-1\"\u003ephp\u003c/p\u003e\n      \u003c/button\u003e\n\n   \u003cdiv class=\"tw-flex\"\u003e\n      \u003cbutton \n        class=\"\n          line-number-button\n          tw-mx-2 \n          tw-hidden \n          group-[.is-open]:tw-block \n          group-[.show-line-numbers]:tw-text-fgColor-link \n          print:!tw-hidden\" \n        title=\"Toggle line numbers\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"icon\"\n    xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 512 512\"\u003e\u003c!-- Font Awesome Free 5.15.4 by @fontawesome - https://fontawesome.com License - https://fontawesome.com/license/free (Icons: CC BY 4.0, Fonts: SIL OFL 1.1, Code: MIT License) --\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M61.77 401l17.5-20.15a19.92 19.92 0 0 0 5.07-14.19v-3.31C84.34 356 80.5 352 73 352H16a8 8 0 0 0-8 8v16a8 8 0 0 0 8 8h22.83a157.41 157.41 0 0 0-11 12.31l-5.61 7c-4 5.07-5.25 10.13-2.8 14.88l1.05 1.93c3 5.76 6.29 7.88 12.25 7.88h4.73c10.33 0 15.94 2.44 15.94 9.09 0 4.72-4.2 8.22-14.36 8.22a41.54 41.54 0 0 1-15.47-3.12c-6.49-3.88-11.74-3.5-15.6 3.12l-5.59 9.31c-3.72 6.13-3.19 11.72 2.63 15.94 7.71 4.69 20.38 9.44 37 9.44 34.16 0 48.5-22.75 48.5-44.12-.03-14.38-9.12-29.76-28.73-34.88zM496 224H176a16 16 0 0 0-16 16v32a16 16 0 0 0 16 16h320a16 16 0 0 0 16-16v-32a16 16 0 0 0-16-16zm0-160H176a16 16 0 0 0-16 16v32a16 16 0 0 0 16 16h320a16 16 0 0 0 16-16V80a16 16 0 0 0-16-16zm0 320H176a16 16 0 0 0-16 16v32a16 16 0 0 0 16 16h320a16 16 0 0 0 16-16v-32a16 16 0 0 0-16-16zM16 160h64a8 8 0 0 0 8-8v-16a8 8 0 0 0-8-8H64V40a8 8 0 0 0-8-8H32a8 8 0 0 0-7.14 4.42l-8 16A8 8 0 0 0 24 64h8v64H16a8 8 0 0 0-8 8v16a8 8 0 0 0 8 8zm-3.91 160H80a8 8 0 0 0 8-8v-16a8 8 0 0 0-8-8H41.32c3.29-10.29 48.34-18.68 48.34-56.44 0-29.06-25-39.56-44.47-39.56-21.36 0-33.8 10-40.46 18.75-4.37 5.59-3 10.84 2.8 15.37l8.58